    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nWhen writing custom diagnostics handlers such as [lsp_lines](https://git.sr.ht/~whynothugo/lsp_lines.nvim) it would be useful to reuse functions such as `filter_by_severity`, `prefix_source` etc which are in core instead of rewriting/copying them. See eg [this thread](https://lists.sr.ht/~whynothugo/lsp_lines.nvim/%3C168064285846.29839.2062340608224481405-0%40git.sr.ht%3E#%3C20230405112335.h4e5yo63sn4awm76@hyperion.whynothugo.nl%3E).\r\n\r\nWould it make sense to make the following functions in `runtime/lua/vim/diagnostic.lua` public?\r\n* `filter_by_severity`\r\n* `count_sources`\r\n* `prefix_source`\r\n* `reformat_diagnostics`\r\n\r\nAlternatively one could expose functions at one abstraction higher, such as:\r\n```lua\r\n\r\nM.format = function(bufnr, diagnostics, opts)\r\n  if opts.format then\r\n    diagnostics = reformat_diagnostics(opts.format, diagnostics)\r\n  end\r\n  if\r\n    opts.source\r\n    and (opts.source ~= 'if_many' or count_sources(bufnr) > 1)\r\n  then\r\n    diagnostics = prefix_source(diagnostics)\r\n  end\r\n  return diagnostics\r\nend\r\n```\r\n\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nSee above",
